                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.105A/11–2944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-29T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 29, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>697. British Embassy here has again raised question of possibility of Schwarzkopf
                    assuming jurisdiction over Iranian police. Imminent arrival in Tehran of Major
                    Preston after having discussed this and other <hi rend="italic">gendarmerie</hi>
                    problems in Washington offers good opportunity to discuss question with
                    Schwarzkopf with idea of arriving at a definite decision. Dept has no desire to
                    put pressure on Iranian Government to accept Schwarzkopf or any other American
                    as police adviser. However, it is understood that Iranian Government has already
                    made tentative approach to Schwarzkopf on subject so that renewal of the
                    discussions at Schwarzkopf’s instance could not be considered as pressure from
                    this end. Please discuss with Schwarzkopf and with Iranian Government if you
                    deem advisable and give Dept benefit of your recommendations. You may inform
                    Schwarzkopf that Dept will support with War his recommendations for increase in
                    staff to meet the added work and responsibility entailed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
